@endnode

@node Allgemeines

      General
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
    With TAB / Shift-TAB you get from one stringgadget to the next/last
    gadget.

    Underscored letters mean that you can select the gadget by the under-
    scored key also.

    Passwords:  The EDIT-Function and all the Gadgets can be protected
    ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ  with a password. If NO Password should be checked, the
                entry in the Stringgadget must be EMPTY (no Spaces !).
                The Passwords can be max. 10 chars.

                The Password-check offers no real protection, but a
                "non-freak" shouldn't be able to get to the appropriate
                program and most important, to the EDIT-Function (useful
                if the Computer is accessible by the public).

                CAUTION: Don't forget your Passwords !
                         Remember the Case-Sensitivity !
                         When entering the Passwords, someone could read
                         them!

@endnode

@node Spalten-Titel

      The four Column-titles
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
Can be changed by entering the new titles and pressing return.

@endnode

@node CreateTitle

The CreateTitle-Gadget
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

By clicking on this gadget, the filename of the program will be
copied to the Gadget-title. No need to type it on your own !

However, this doesn't work satisfying with all filenames.

@endnode

@node Listen-Gadget

      The Listview-Gadgets
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
The four listview-gadgets represent the four gadget-columns. You can select
the gadget to be edited in these lists or by using the "Select" gadget
from which you can select the gadget directly from the main-screen.


@endnode

@node Programmtyp

      The Program-type
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
Now you choose the program-type-mode with the four small radio-buttons.
You can choose

      Normal: For executable programs (shell)

       WBRUN: For executable programs (Workbench). WBRun should be used
              for all programs that can be started from Workbench.
              Informations from the Icon of the program (Tooltypes)
              will be used.

       Batch: For Batchfiles, these are started with "Execute <file>".
              (You don't have to specify the "execute"). E.g. the
              startup-sequence is called a "Batch".

       ARexx: For ARexx-Programs. These are started with "rx <file>".
              Rx must be in a drawer which has been marked with "path"
              (see DOS-Documentation).
@endnode

@node Programmstart-Gadget

      The Programstart-mode
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
Now you have to select the @{"programstart-mode" link Programmstart-Modus} with the other
radio-buttons. If you choose "None", the gadget has (even if there's a
title and/or filename) no function. Use it to create "empty" gadgets.


@endnode

@node Darstellungs-Gadget

      The Look-Gadget
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
It's for viewing the look of the selected gadget. Sometimes, this gadget
is too small and the look is not the same as the real gadget (to large
fonts etc...)

@endnode

@node Farbauswahl-Gadget

      The Color-Gadget
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
With this, you can select the background color for the selected gadget.
Depending on the number of colors of the screen, the selection is smaller
or larger.

It may happen that this gadget has too many entries].


@endnode

@node Schriftfarb-Gadget

The font-color gadget
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

Here you can set the fontcolor for the gadgettitle of the active gadget-
entry.

Depending on the number of colors of the screen, the selection is smaller
or larger.

It may happen that this gadget has too many entries].

@endnode

@node Schriften-Listen-Gadget

      The Fontlist-Gadget
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
In this Listview-gadget you can select one of the six fonts for the
selected gadget.


@endnode

@node Schrift-Gadget

       The Font-Gadget
       ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
Here you can set one of the six fonts and their size. To do this, select
the font to be changed in the Fontlist-Gadget and then click on this
gadget. A Fontrequester appears where you can choose any font with any
size. If the size you want is not available, you can select it by specifying
the size manually in the stringgadget (Font-Scaling - doesn't look very
nice but saves diskspace).

@endnode

@node CopySwapDelete-Gadget

       The Copy/Swap/Delete-Gadgets
       ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
With those gadgets you can Copy, Swap or Delete Gadgets. To do this:
Copy: Select the gadget to be copied - Copy - Select destination.
Swap: Select first gadget - Swap - Select second gadget.
Delete: Select the gadget to be deleted - Delete.

Hint: Use the keyboard-shortcuts for these functions. Instead of
clicking, just type "c","s","d" respectively.

@endnode

@node Iff-Brush

IFF-Brushes
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

In the textgadget named "IFF-Brush" you can type in the filename of an
IFF-Brush. Every gadget can have its own brush. This IFF-brush will be
displayed as set with the @{" BrushMode-Gadget " link BrushMode}.

You can still overlay the brush with a gadget-title !

IFF-Brushes can be created by using painting-programs. They shouldn't
have more than 16 colors, since HDClick doesn't use more.

If you want to create your own brushes you should look that you create
"real" brushes, and not whole images. You can save brushes usually with
functions that say "SAVE BRUSH". A brush is not an entire image but a
"part" of an image which you have cut out with the "cut-tool" or
something.

Also you must take care to use the same palette in your paint-program
that you have on your HDClick-screen. If you don't, the brushes won't
have the right colors.

@endnode

@node BrushMode

The BrushMode-gadget
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

With this you can set the way brushes are displayed for the active
gadget-entry.

Pattern:
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
The Brush is used to "fill" the entire gadget, even if it's smaller than
the gadget. Small brushes save memory, but be careful, too small brushes
need a lot of time to display !

Center:
ŻŻŻŻŻŻ
The brush is displayed once in the center of the gadget. The background-
color of the gadget will also be visible if the brush is smaller than
the gadget.

Left:
ŻŻŻŻ

The brush is displayed once in the upper left corner of the gadget.

@endnode



@node EasyEdit

       The EasyEdit Gadget
       ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
After pressing this gadget, an Appwindow is opened on Workbench. If you
drag one Icon in this Window, the Path and Filename of this Icon will be
given to the Filename of the selected Gadget. This is an alternative to
the Filerequester-gadget.

If you drag more than one icon into the Window, their filenames will be
"transmitted" to the following gadget(s). This way you can drag as many
icons into the window as there are gadgets available after the gadget
you have selected before you clicked on "EasyEdit".

The gadgets also automatically get a gadget-title and a useful start-
and program-mode (WBRUN and Run) so that after "Save"/"Use" you can
already start those programs by clicking on the gadgets.

Example : If you choose the first gadget in the first listgadget you
can drag 45 Icons into the window which will close automatically afterwards.
So you have now configured 45 gadgets that can immediately be used !

With the CLOSEgadget you get back to the EDIT-window.

If you have accidently overwritten previously configured gadgets by
dragging icons into the window, you can always press "Reload" to get back
to your last saved config.

@endnode

@node Farben-Gadget

       The Palette-Gadget
       ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
You can specify the screencolors for EACH configfile !


@endnode

@node Small-Gadget

       The Small-Gadget
       ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
Another window ist opened, where you can specify the X and Y-coordinates,
height and width and the Font for the small-window.


@endnode

@node AppIcon

       The AppIcon-Gadget
       ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
Here, you can specify the X and Y-coordinates of the AppIcon. Also, you can
specify a Launcher-Program. This can be a Graphic-Viewer, a decruncher
or a text-viewer. The best tool for this is "MultiView" from WB3.0 which
detects different filetypes (unfortunately, I don't own it). Important:
The char @ must be used! The @ will be replaced by the filename of the
Icon dragged onto the AppIcon. Example: "Dh0:Utilities/Display @"


@endnode

@node Stack

Set the Stack
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

The number entered in this textgadget will be used as the stack for the
program. It has to be at least 4096 bytes.

If you use @{" WBRun " link ProgrammTyp}, the stack entered here will not
be used, instead the program will use the stack mentioned in its icon.

@endnode

@node Preferences-Gadget

       The Preferences-Gadget
       ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
More Informations about this Window in (6) "Preferences".


@endnode

@node Hilfe-Gadget

       The Help-Gadget
       ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
This is the Online-Help. When this mode is activated, any gadget can be
selected and the appropriate help-message will be displayed. To quit the
help-mode, click onto the Help-Gadget again.

@endnode

@node Reload-Gadget

       The Reload-Gadget
       ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
This reloads the Configfile without asking. All changes will be lost.


@endnode

@node Speichern

       Saving
       ŻŻŻŻŻŻ
All changes (also from Prefs, SmallPrefs and AppIconPrefs etc.) are saved.
Two files are written:

1. The actual configfile with all Gadgets and Column-titles
2. A Preferences-file with global settings

@endnode

@node SpeichernAls-Gadget

       The Save As Gadget
       ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
You can save the Configfile with another name. With this, you can create
new configfiles easily.

The @{"Preferences" link Preferences} are also saved, but to the place it was loaded from.


@endnode

@node BackPattern

The Background-Pattern
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

The IFF-Brush entered in this gadget will be used as a background-pattern
in HDClick's mainwindow.

The brush will be used to "fill" the entire screen. A Small brush saves
memory, but it will take longer to display. With a big screen
this might take very long !

Hint 1:

You could use a black square IFF-Brush to change the background-color
of HDClick.

Hint 2:

Don't use this function at all, since the brush is not visible a lot
because there's not much space left between the gadgets.

@endnode

@node Preferences

                                Preferences
                                ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
By Clicking onto the "Prefs"-Gadget in the EDIT-Window, the Prefs are
opened.

An Online-help is available ! You can end the modus by pressing on the
Help-button again. "HDCHelp" must be in the actual drawer for this function.

@{" HDClick-Startmode        " link Startmodus}
@{" Iconify mode             " link Iconifymodus}
@{" Window-coordinates       " link Fenster-Positionen}
@{" Color specifications     " link AnzahlFarben}
@{" Screenmode               " link Screenmodus}
@{" Screen-Appearance        " link ScreenAufbau}

@endnode

@node Startmodus

      The HDClick-Startmode
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
      Not to be confounded with the Program-startmode (Launch , Run etc.).
      Here you can specify in which form HDClick will be started:
      -  Normal: HDClick opens the Mainwindow
      -   Small: HDClick opens the Small-Window
      - Iconify: HDClick opens the Iconify-Window

      The changes get active as soon as HDClick is started again.

@endnode

@node Iconifymodus

(6.2) The HDClick-Iconify-mode
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
      More Infos about the @{"Iconify-modes" link Iconify-Funktion}.

      If you press the right Mousebutton in the @{"Mainscreen" link Haupt-Screen} or @{"Small-Window" link Small},
      an Iconify-Window appears. This can be changed in this version of
      HDClick. You can chose between
                     -  Window: The Iconify-Window opens
                     - AppIcon: The @{"AppIcon" link AppIcon} is opened.
                     -  @{"Hotkey" link Hotkey}: No Window opens. HDClick is still in memory.
      Back to the Mainscreen you get by pressing the key specified in the
      @{"TOOLTYPES" link Tooltypes}. This is good for people who have too many Iconify
      Windows (inclusive clocks etc.) on their screen.

@endnode

@node Fenster-Positionen

      The Window-Coordinates
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
      Here you can specify the X/Y coordinates of the @{"Iconify - Window" link Iconify-Funktion}.

@endnode

@node AnzahlFarben

      Color specifications
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
      Here you can select how many colors the screen should have. Maximum
      is 16 colors.

@endnode

@node Screenmodus

      The Screenmode
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
      You can choose between WB Clone and Custom. If WB Clone is used, the
      HDClick Screen will use the settings in Workbench's Preferences,
      so it will have the same Size, Colors and Modes as the Workbench-
      Screen.
      When you choose custom, you can select an own screenmode. You can
      do this by clicking on "Screenmode...". A window with a list of
      all available Screenmodes appears, of which you can select one.

@endnode

@node ScreenAufbau

      The Screen-Appearance
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
      You can select how the Screen should appear:

      -    Normal: The Screen is opened immediately and the Gadget-drawing
                   is visible.

      -    Hidden: The Gadgets are drawn in the background. After that, the
                   Screen comes to the front.

      - Scroll1&2: The Gadgets are drawn in the background. After that, the
                   Screen scrolls up. Two speeds are available.

An Online-help is available ! You can end the modus by pressing on the
Help-button again. "HDCHelp" must be in the actual drawer for this function.

@endnode

@node Programmstart-Modus

                            Programmstart-Modus
                            ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{" Launch  " link Launch}
@{" Run     " link Run}
@{" Execute " link Execute}
@{" WBFront " link WBFront}
@{" Option  " link Option}
@{" Menu    " link Menue}

@endnode

@node Launch

      Mode Launch:
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
            In the mode Launch the program will be started normally
            and HDClick quits.


@endnode

@node Run

      Mode Run:
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
            In the mode Run, the program will be started with RUN. HDClick
            closes the screen and iconifies.

@endnode

@node Execute

      Mode Execute:
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

            In the mode Execute, the program will be started with RUN. The
            HDClick-screen stays open, other programs can be started by
            clicking on gadgets.
            The Mode "Execute" has NOTHING to do with the CLI-command
            "Execute" which executes batchfiles.

@endnode

@node WBFront

      Mode WBFront:
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
            With this mode, a program is started and the HDClick-Screen
            goes behind all other screens. By pressing the hotkey, the
            screen pops to the front again very fast. Use this mode instead
            of "Run" if you have enough Chipmemory.


@endnode

@node Menue

(7.4) Mode Menu:
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
            In the mode Menu, a new configfile will be loaded after the
            gadget has been selected. All gadgets,titles and the Prefs-
            specifications will change to the entries specified in the
            new configfile. The filename of the configfile to load must
            stand at the same place as a Program-Filename.

            Here an example for an entry for Gadget in the EDIT-Window:

                  Title: Graphic
            Configfiles: Dh0:s/graphicconfig
                   Mode: Menu

            After this gadget has been selected, the configfile
            "Dh0:s/GraphicConfig" will be loaded. All gadgets will now
            become new functions, declared in the new-loaded configfile
            ("GraphicConfig"). If the Configfile wasn't found after
            clicking on the Gadget, a requester appears. By selecting
            "Create New", a new configfile with the Filename specified
            before will be created. In the example above, the Configfile
            "Dh0:s/GraphicConfig" would be created.

            With this function you have access on an unlimited number of
            configfiles. In a submenu there can be more submenus, the next
            can also have submenus and so on. You can get from each menu
            to all other menus, if the gadgets have been declared for that.
            See "Examples" for more details.

How to create a new Configfile
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
            The fastest way to do this is by using Save AS in the @{"Edit" link EDIT-Funktion}-
            Window or copying an existing Configfile.

@endnode

@node Option

(7.6) Mode Option:
      ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

            In the mode Option, a window opens:

The stringgadget:

            The text which is typed in there will be received as an
            argument by the declared program. Example:

            Entry in the configfile:          Text in the stringgadget:
                      |                                   |
             "dh0:c/Ed,Editor,o"               "dh0:s/startup-sequence"
                      |___________________________________|
                                        |
                           Following will be executed:
                                        |
                         "dh0:c/Ed dh0:s/startup-sequence"

            The editor "ed" loads the text-file "dh0:s/startup-
            sequence".

            When one of the following gadgets is clicked on, the
            defined program will be started (see above) with one
            of the @{"Programstart-modes" link Programmstart-Modus}, depending on which gadget
            you click.

@endnode

